make double-click select decimal numbers like 123.45 (fixes #4999)  Previously would only select 123 or 45
Command Palette: add ":" option that shows everytihng like 3.5 (fixes #5031)
in Command Palette, when viewing opened files history (#), you can press Delete to remove the entry from history (fixes #5025)
Djvu: guard DataPool::create() against invalid data (fixes #5035)
fix gLangsMap to be strseq compatible  forgot to add terminating 0
fortify management of Wnd,HWND map for message reflection  trying to track down/fix issues with TabCtrl handling messages after being destroyed
maybe fix a crash in URLEncodeMayTruncateTemp()
Update darkmodelib and enabled its support for light themes
maybe fix show logs and open advanced settings in store build
fix path to versions.txt in project files
make URLEncodeTemp() not fail for large urls but truncate (fixes #4547)  Was making "translate selection with Google etc." not work on large selections
don't use different data directory for store build; make them inter-changeable
remove bogus ReportIf()  here we didn't have a history for the file because it was opened for a -plugin and with some temporary path.
Improve theme for menu and toolbar for older OS
tweak highlight notifications colors for themes (fixes #4980)  They were hardcoded to yellow for bg and red for txt for non-default theme derive them from main background / text color
improve tab dragging (fixes #4983)  a silly logic would only start drag with visual feedback if mouse moved outside of tab area, which made moving just left and right not work well
simplify TabsCtrl WM_LBUTTONDOWN handling with early return
add logging for tabs mouse handling crash #4982  rename WndMapGetWindow() => WndMapFindByHWND()
no update checks for store build
dont upload ReportIf() in store build

don't require pressing Enter for upload
add darkmodelib files to SumatraPDF-dll project

add darkmodelib files to the project
Apply full dark mode on dark themes
add logvf() for verbose logging; remove NO_LOG; add BlittableBitmapByteSize()  and RenderCache::LogCacheSize()
move RenderCacheThread out of RenderCache class

Revert "fix order of rendering with predictive rendering (fixes #4584)"  This reverts commit 5645875de18fb6791030c2b17ac861fd19a900ff.
Revert "add logvf(), remove NO_LOG; log size of bitmap cache in RenderCache"  This reverts commit 8218cf8c6f472a586f5d3a2fd99827b98c674eae.
logview-web: convert top buttons to dropdown menu at top right
add logvf(), remove NO_LOG; log size of bitmap cache in RenderCache
logview-web: add support for v: values

fix order of rendering with predictive rendering (fixes #4584)  I mistakenly commented out a code that ensured that when we queue pages for rendering, the visible page would be rendered before before / after page from preditictive rendering. Tweaked RenderCache logging. Made CONSERVE_MEMORY a runtime time switch instead of only compile time. Renamed DisplayModel::dontRenderFlag => pauseRendering.
update keyboard shortcuts docs  `i` and `Shift - i` swapped place in 3.6
logview-web: use explicit featch() of logs instead of server side events  makes things more robust
logview-web: move server .go code to ./server sub-directory
logview: use virtual list to improve performance for large logs
change filteredLogs to be arry of numbers
add button to generate lots of test data
encode server side event data as json
implement basic sending of pipe logs to the server via server side events
re-org files to make bun run build work
improve next / prev file in directory when files are renamed and deleted (fixes #4588)

allow print dialog even if configured for no disk access (fixes #4739)  The justification for not showing printer dialog was that it can allow access to file system but since we have PrinterAccess, it should just cover this

make -uninstall flag work even if file name as -install in it (fixes #4601)  if file has "-install" in it, we would auto-deduce it's an installer and run installer logic before checking for explicit -uninstall flag
maybe fix crash when dragging tabs (for #4572)
optimize GetFileState() to only open file once, not twice (for #4635)
with EscToExit when in fullscreen Esc only ends fullscreen  Would exit the app before. Now you have to press Esc again.
fix another potential crash in previews (for #4875)
fix potential crash in preview handlers (fixes #4875)
use SegoeUI windows font for Hebrew (fixes #4939)
improve CollectNextPrevFilesIfChanged() by correctly comparing directories (for #4940)
don't corrupt long file paths \\?\ in ParseFileArgs (fixes #4947)
Open Explorer and select file  Instead of just opening the directory, this selects the file. This helps if you have a folder with lots of similarly named file.
Partial Revert of "fix color invert in default theme" (fixes #4073)

fix crash caused by libchm (fixes #4937)  Thanks to Joseph Kiriacos for bug report and test file. You can craft .chm file where block_len would pass > UINT_MAX test and then we would crash in _chm_decompress_block because block_len + 6144 would overflow, cbuffer would be too small and memory would be over-written in _chm_fetch_bytes
